1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,060

2
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:49,460

3
00:00:49,460 --> 00:00:55,960

4
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:58,780
 There was a 50% off sale sign in front of the store.

5
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:01,300
 It's perfect for our baby,so I bought one.

6
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:04,340
But we don't even know if it's a boy or a girl yet.

7
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:09,430
 It's a girl who resembles you. I say that every day while tapping on my tummy.

8
00:01:09,430 --> 00:01:12,850
A girl shouldn't look like me.

9
00:01:12,850 --> 00:01:14,590
The chairman must be here.

10
00:01:14,590 --> 00:01:16,390
 Yes, I'm nearby, too.

11
00:01:16,390 --> 00:01:18,750
- See you later. 
  - Bye.

12
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:20,360
Yes.

13
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:24,760
- Hello. 
 - Hi.

14
00:01:43,050 --> 00:01:47,530
Oh, so the Ministry of Food and Drug Safety gave the final approval?

15
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:49,320
Yes, yes, we will announce it tomorrow morning.

16
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:54,350
It's only for adults with ADHD, and if it's proven effective, we will add more patient categories.

17
00:01:54,350 --> 00:02:01,530
Good work. I was getting concerned, wondering if I have to take all those Next pills piled in the warehouse.

18
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:04,700
Thanks to you, I will be making money again, Director Han.

19
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:10,070
It failed as a treatment for pneumonia, but I believe it's plausible for adult ADHD.

20
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:14,820
Yes, yes. The word is already out that it increases the ability to concentrate.

21
00:02:14,820 --> 00:02:18,090
Quite a few people around me are already taking it.

22
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:25,860
- Is it Next? 
 - Yes.

23
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:28,260
- Have you not tried it, Director Han? 
 - No.

24
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:34,150
Try taking it when you're feeling tired. I feel alive. It's excellent.

25
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:44,890
Hello.

26
00:02:44,890 --> 00:02:47,140
Hello, I'm Park Young In.

27
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:50,390
I heard a lot about you. Please take a seat.

28
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:52,880
- Is that it? 
 - Yes.

29
00:02:56,040 --> 00:03:00,790
So are you having a prince or a princess?

30
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:03,460
Our baby? I think it's a girl.

31
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:08,630
Aigoo. That's great. They say having one daughter is better than ten sons these days.

32
00:03:08,630 --> 00:03:10,830
That's what everyone says.

33
00:03:10,830 --> 00:03:13,160
- Excuse me. 
 - Sure.

34
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:18,410
Then when do we get to meet your princess?

35
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:23,230
I'm at twelve weeks right now so probably in about six months?

36
00:03:23,230 --> 00:03:25,040
Biting people?

37
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,390
Are you sure they didn't take some other drugs?

38
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:32,360
We are announcing the final approval tomorrow.

39
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:36,210
Check him into the hospital and make sure no one talks. The rumor can't get out.

40
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:44,040
It's not like they died. Who cares? Just offer treatment cost and compensation then!

41
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:49,080
I'll call you back.

42
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,390
Honey...

43
00:04:31,030 --> 00:04:33,420
The prime minister's office is summoning you.

44
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:53,410
Where is it going?

45
00:04:53,410 --> 00:04:59,080
The landfill. We lack facilities for mild case patients.

46
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:09,490
Do you still not understand what I'm doing?

47
00:05:12,130 --> 00:05:13,920
No, Sir.

48
00:05:15,150 --> 00:05:20,040
I made the choice, at which point I'll prevent further damage.

49
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:25,770
You'll soon have to decide how far you'll get your hands bloodied, Lieutenant Lee.

50
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:28,460
How did the treatment drug work?

51
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:34,890
We sorted biotherapeutics and injected them into the infected, but they all died.

52
00:05:37,550 --> 00:05:42,650
Do it again. Until it works. I'll buy us time.

53
00:05:51,590 --> 00:06:00,060

54
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,300

55
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,380
What do we do then?

56
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:09,260
You're saying Madman Rabies patients are right outside, but we won't be getting help from the authorities.

57
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:12,390
We have to force our way out then!

58
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:15,250
They even installed fences along the walls.

59
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,870
Even if we make it out, where are we supposed to go?

60
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:22,790
We just have to get out first and go into the most expensive apartment.

61
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:27,820
What can they do then? Will they lock that down too? With a bunch of high and mighty people living there?

62
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:32,690
The reason they're doing this to us is that our apartments are cheap.

63
00:06:33,610 --> 00:06:37,400
But are you sure the patients are outside?

64
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:41,030
Building Representative and Oh Joo Hyung are both absent.

65
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:43,310
Are you implying that it's just the renters that are here again?

66
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:50,080
I'm trying to say that most of the people who left the building are absent.

67
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,700
If you want to go outside, go ahead.

68
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,970
I can't guarantee that you'll make it back, though.

69
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:59,820
Then I'll assume that all of you understand.

70
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:06,380
The food and other items we brought from the supermarket are in unit 201. Go there if you need anything.

71
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:12,930
But I'm sure they are lacking something, too, so please exchange it for whatever they need.

72
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:20,960
If the infected people's symptoms get worse, what if they break in through the doors?

73
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:24,430
If they hit it with a car or something, it'll break since it's a glass door.

74
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:27,590
They'll probably find an easier way to get inside instead.

75
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:30,060
That's how a crime always starts out.

76
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:36,790
"I went in because the door was left open, I took the bike because there was no lock on it..."

77
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:39,950
But "I want to break in because I'm craving blood"...

78
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:42,470
To come to that decision is tougher than you think.

79
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:46,220
It means, as long as you don't give them a reason to...

80
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:50,050
All the doors have been locked...

81
00:07:57,150 --> 00:07:58,820
Why?

82
00:07:59,630 --> 00:08:01,460
The rooftop.

83
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:09,490
I'm the only one here.

84
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,190
Do you think he heard us?

85
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:29,390
I hope not.

86
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:47,890
Andrew, you never get startled. Outside or here.

87
00:08:49,090 --> 00:08:53,650
I'm just happy that people don't see me as weird.

88
00:08:53,650 --> 00:08:55,530
Be careful, both of you.

89
00:08:55,530 --> 00:08:57,600
You, too, Andrew.

90
00:09:04,930 --> 00:09:07,900
Let's take a breather before we go back in.

91
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:15,200
I'm so tired.

92
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:26,130
This reminds me of the old days, standing here like this.

93
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:27,760
When?

94
00:09:29,890 --> 00:09:32,940
That day? Hey.

95
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:37,430
Gosh, I wondered momentarily if I could fly that day.

96
00:09:37,430 --> 00:09:39,300
You did fly.

97
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,260
I did.

98
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:47,790
If I could fly, I would go to my mom's nursing home.

99
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:53,170
It was uncomfortable to go see her so I kept postponing it, and here we are.

100
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:59,830
I wonder what happened to all the infected people.

101
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:04,030
Are they hiding somewhere and holding back their thirst?

102
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:06,120
They're probably scared.

103
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:11,630
Afraid that they'll bite someone closest to them. Afraid that they'll completely turn into monsters.

104
00:10:12,860 --> 00:10:17,730
But I'm sure they'll fight until they're defeated by their thirst.

105
00:10:17,730 --> 00:10:20,060
Everyone should be okay, right?

106
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:26,040
Of course. We just have to make sure not to get hurt so we can meet them again healthy.

107
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,960
So don't do that kind of stuff ever again.

108
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:33,550
Hey! We have no idea what kind of blood that is. Why would you get it on your hands?

109
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:37,540
But it's okay that I put it on Oh Joo Hyung's face?

110
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:40,270
Well, it's not like you made him eat it.

111
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:42,800
I doubt he would lick that blood.

112
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,300
He would never do that.

113
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:48,290
Gosh, it seemed like he really cares about his health.

114
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:53,580
Seeing that he didn't come down earlier, I think he feels a bit intimidated now.

115
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:56,280
Now that I think about it, the Building Rep didn't show up, either, right?

116
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:12,640
Are you okay?

117
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,650
Of course, I'm not okay.

118
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,870
Look at this.

119
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:29,220
I must've been so shocked for this to happen... Darn.

120
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:34,000
Maybe it's best to give up, given what happened.

121
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:38,500
Looking at the state of things, it doesn't seem like you would make that much money by being the resident representative.

122
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:42,780
And if we move? If we move now, this place would be worth nothing. Dirt cheap.

123
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:46,880
So you want us to lose money by leaving here and starting over at another apartment?

124
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:49,350
I'm saying it because there's no other way.

125
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:52,090
You said you think Seung Beom at the gym seems infected, too.

126
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:55,300
You went to the gym every day. What did you do there?

127
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,820
You should have monitored stuff like that.

128
00:11:59,230 --> 00:12:01,620
I had no idea he would do that.

129
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:09,780
When the lockdown is lifted, the entire apartment complex will need some repair.

130
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:15,560
I'll change the elevator's interior, and I'll suggest getting rid of the outer wall.

131
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,500
The lockdown was easier because of that wall.

132
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,710
Let's also suggest that we plant some trees around the perimeter.

133
00:12:22,710 --> 00:12:24,950
You said you know a landscaping company, right?

134
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:29,630
We can sterilize the whole place since there were infected people.

135
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:33,770
That's right! That's it!

136
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:39,230
Once we think differently, there are plenty of ideas.

137
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:45,410
But do you think you can become the resident's representative?

138
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:52,820
I'll recruit some people who are influential in the building.

139
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:56,070
 My father was a schizophrenic.

140
00:12:56,070 --> 00:12:57,860
 He passed away two years ago.

141
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:02,770
 I get shocked easily if I see a similar type of illness.

142
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:05,410
Unni isn't home right now.

143
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:09,330
Darn it.

144
00:13:11,210 --> 00:13:14,520
I see. You're the child from unit 502.

145
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:17,510
 So are you home alone?

146
00:13:17,510 --> 00:13:19,950
 Where are the people from unit 501?

147
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:23,840
- Can you open the door for a second? 
 - The people from Unit 501 are here.

148
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,760
That scared me.

149
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:34,430
I'm sorry about what happened earlier.

150
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:43,060
But you know, you should have explained properly that you're fine.

151
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:46,410
Anyone would misunderstand seeing the blood.

152
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:48,650
Don't you think so?

153
00:13:48,650 --> 00:13:50,860
It's tough for you, too, isn't it?

154
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:54,050
But what a relief that there is someone taking care of you.

155
00:13:54,050 --> 00:13:56,090
It is a huge relief.

156
00:13:56,090 --> 00:13:59,890
That we are on the lower floors.

157
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:11,480
With all this going on, you must be so disappointed that you can't enjoy being newlyweds.

158
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:17,760
My husband and I started on the first floor of a villa.

159
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:21,290
And of all days, there was a flood.

160
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:24,090
When I think back to how much we suffered...

161
00:14:24,090 --> 00:14:26,750
How did you two meet?

162
00:14:28,230 --> 00:14:30,370
Oh, my goodness.

163
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:42,370
You two must go back pretty far.

164
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:47,990
Please have a seat over there.

165
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:57,590
- I can't trust that ahjumma. 
 - Me, neither.

166
00:14:57,590 --> 00:14:59,900
So why did you bring her in?

167
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:04,130
"Keep your friends close, your enemies closer."

168
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:10,040
Hey, where is Sae Bom?

169
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:14,080
She's talking to the building representative. She says she came by to apologize.

170
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,540
Apologize?

171
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:18,420
- I'm sure even her apology makes you feel angry. 
 - Yeah!

172
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:20,830
It's because she's not sorry.

173
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:25,630
But she asked me if I was aiming to become the resident's representative.

174
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:28,430
- So that's what she's after. 
 - Why would you want to? It'd be such a hassle.

175
00:15:28,430 --> 00:15:30,130
She spoke like you would make tons of money.

176
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:34,630
Hey, from the management office to outside services, the representative signs off on all those contracts.

177
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,890
The elevator, outer wall, rooftop, parking, electricity, landscaping.

178
00:15:36,890 --> 00:15:40,250
- Everything. All of that is money. 
 - Everything?

179
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,900
Don't you have any more?

180
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:47,170
I'm an athlete, after all.

181
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:48,860
Give me one more kimbap.

182
00:15:48,860 --> 00:15:51,000
- Kimbap? 
 - Yes.

183
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:54,300
Wait.

184
00:15:55,050 --> 00:15:57,600
Ahjussi, are you going to handcuff me again today?

185
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,030
I'm losing blood circulation.

186
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,960
- Kim Seung Beom. 
 - Yes.

187
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:09,260
All the residents here are hyper-anxious.

188
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:11,120
They don't know so they let it slide until now.

189
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:14,890
But soon, people will start being suspicious about your condition.

190
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:16,880
So?

191
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:24,060
I'm asking you to be cautious so people won't get scared.

192
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,990
I can't keep you uncuffed today,

193
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:34,050
but if you're okay for a few more days, I'll let you roam around the gym freely.

194
00:16:35,190 --> 00:16:38,700
You're not threatening me today...

195
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:44,760
I'm just hoping you're not infected, Kim Seung Beom.

196
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:50,620
Even without your issue, there are tons of other problems in this building.

197
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:01,420
Seriously! Gosh! S***!

198
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:05,690
I'm going to kill him! Wait and see!

199
00:17:26,570 --> 00:17:28,730
Why are you looking at me like that? I'm fine.

200
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:31,590
Hey, hey, look. All clear, right?

201
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:33,580
You seem to be the one who is scared.

202
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:35,960
You were basically washing your skin off.

203
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:42,630
Hey! Hey, hey, what are you taking?

204
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:45,990

205
00:17:45,990 --> 00:17:49,190
I thought you were taking something weird and unhealthy.

206
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:51,020
Pour me a drink.

207
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:07,010
You saw Min Ji taking medicine at the clinic, huh?

208
00:18:07,010 --> 00:18:10,430
Like supplements or a pick-me-up.

209
00:18:10,430 --> 00:18:12,720
She did take something now and then when she got tired.

210
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:14,590
Which medicine?

211
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:17,530
I don't know. It was some type of pill.

212
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:22,230
She said it was a health supplement she got from her gym.

213
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:24,860
The gym?

214
00:18:24,860 --> 00:18:27,200
 Moreover, I didn't see your name on the gym entry log.

215
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:30,050
 My wife used to go to that gym.

216
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:33,930
 Did the Madness Rabies start at the gym?

217
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,540
Why? Is it something important?

218
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:43,490
Go easy on the alcohol. It's not good for you.

219
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,650
Where are you going?

220
00:18:45,650 --> 00:18:48,250
Somewhere. Don't worry about it.

221
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,760

222
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:24,240

223
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:29,430

224
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:48,020
- You go ahead, Hyung. 
 - Why?

225
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,330
I left my wallet.

226
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:53,030
Why do you carry your wallet?

227
00:19:53,030 --> 00:19:55,820
I'll be right back. Go on ahead.

228
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:05,490

229
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,280
Who is there?

230
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:21,180
You're really here like this.

231
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:26,680
Ahjussi, are you stuck here?

232
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:30,340
Yes, well. I'm stuck here.

233
00:20:30,340 --> 00:20:33,760
The cop from the fifth floor locked me up here.

234
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:37,320
Ahjussi, please help me.

235
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:41,360
There's really nothing wrong with me.

236
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:45,790
I'm totally fine, but that cop living upstairs...

237
00:20:45,790 --> 00:20:49,350
- That cop– 
 - You sold

238
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:51,520
drugs to my wife, didn't you?

239
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:56,370
The woman doctor from the sixth floor. The one who died from Madman Rabies.

240
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:07,170
I'm not here to threaten you, nor to take revenge, either.

241
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:14,900
I'm just grateful to you.

242
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,800
Ahjussi.

243
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:21,180
I want to buy that drug.

244
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:25,030
I really don't know anything.

245
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:29,200
- You don't know? 
 - I really don't know!

246
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:32,720
- You really don't know? 
 - I don't know!

247
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,110
- You don't know? 
 - I don't!

248
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:36,520
Geez, seriously!

249
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:39,170
You're pissing me off!

