and wished for their recovery.

510
00:41:46,730 --> 00:41:52,060
That's not something you should get thrown out for without treatment.

511
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:56,100
 Well, how is this the same as Covid?

512
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:58,020
It is different.

513
00:41:59,170 --> 00:42:06,410
It makes them attack and bite people. I get that everyone is afraid and anxious. I feel the same way.

514
00:42:06,410 --> 00:42:10,560
But what will happen if it happens

515
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:13,520
to me or my family?

516
00:42:14,340 --> 00:42:19,310
After we throw out trainer Kim Seung Beom, who is next?

517
00:42:19,310 --> 00:42:21,320
Oh Joo Hyung on the sixth floor?

518
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:25,200
Or the attorney who came in contact with Oh Joo Hyung?

519
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:30,500
Should we play musical chairs until only one person remains?

520
00:42:30,500 --> 00:42:32,770
That's enough. Let's vote.

521
00:42:32,770 --> 00:42:35,760
Who agrees that we should throw him out?

522
00:42:41,290 --> 00:42:43,800
We don't necessarily have to throw him outside.

523
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:46,040
I'm just saying let's not have him mingle with the uninfected.

524
00:42:46,040 --> 00:42:51,330
If we lock him up on the rooftop or something and keep us separated, we'll all be safe.

525
00:42:51,330 --> 00:42:53,410
Don't you agree?

526
00:42:54,750 --> 00:42:57,790
Just be yourself and raise your hand comfortably. Why be timid in this day and age?

527
00:42:57,790 --> 00:42:59,790
Hurry and raise your hand.

528
00:42:59,790 --> 00:43:02,030
Go ahead.

529
00:43:05,890 --> 00:43:08,340
Raise your hand. Hurry, hurry.

530
00:43:13,490 --> 00:43:17,160
Ahjumma! How can you do that to me?

531
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:19,150
You're the one who brought me here!

532
00:43:19,150 --> 00:43:23,170
I guess he feels betrayed since I treated him well all this time.

533
00:43:24,610 --> 00:43:27,430
A total of eight people.

534
00:43:28,210 --> 00:43:30,650
So Yoon, what are you doing? Raise your hand.

535
00:43:32,540 --> 00:43:34,270
Hey!

536
00:43:40,130 --> 00:43:42,400
Nine.

537
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:44,770
Those who oppose?

538
00:43:53,110 --> 00:43:56,260
One, two,

539
00:43:56,260 --> 00:43:58,470
three,

540
00:43:58,470 --> 00:44:00,160
four...

541
00:44:01,210 --> 00:44:04,970
five, six...

542
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:07,510
six...

543
00:44:08,650 --> 00:44:10,540
seven,

544
00:44:12,100 --> 00:44:13,980
eight,

545
00:44:17,150 --> 00:44:18,810
nine.

546
00:44:20,820 --> 00:44:23,890
We are tied. What should we do?

547
00:44:23,890 --> 00:44:25,970
Do we vote again?

548
00:44:37,200 --> 00:44:39,860
I don't think we need to.

549
00:44:54,970 --> 00:44:57,610
One vote...

550
00:44:58,430 --> 00:45:00,300
to not throw him out.

551
00:45:10,100 --> 00:45:13,020
Ten votes. It's done.

552
00:45:15,850 --> 00:45:17,670
I'm glad.

553
00:45:17,670 --> 00:45:22,370
I didn't feel good about throwing out someone from our own building.

554
00:45:23,070 --> 00:45:27,610
You know that we have nothing against you, right, Seung Beom?

555
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:33,420
All right then. Let's discuss how we'll monitor Kim Seung Beom.

556
00:45:33,420 --> 00:45:37,890
It's too tough for my husband and me to monitor him along with Detectim Kim Jung Gook.

557
00:45:37,890 --> 00:45:41,620
Let's pair up and check up on Kim Seung Beom.

558
00:45:41,620 --> 00:45:43,660
Who wants to go first?

559
00:45:44,410 --> 00:45:49,790
To follow the rule of democracy, shall we vote?

560
00:45:51,840 --> 00:45:54,220
We'll go first.

561
00:45:59,200 --> 00:46:01,840
 Open up!

562
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,510

563
00:46:05,510 --> 00:46:07,280

564
00:46:07,280 --> 00:46:08,690

565
00:46:08,690 --> 00:46:10,400

566
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:12,880
 Why are you blocking us?

567
00:46:18,910 --> 00:46:19,900
 Why are you doing this?

568
00:46:19,900 --> 00:46:22,200
 What's going on?

569
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:28,400
I heard you suggested to the prime minister's office

570
00:46:28,400 --> 00:46:32,210
to control access to the areas with lots of infected people.

571
00:46:33,460 --> 00:46:38,170
I told them that we cannot stop the infection once the number of infected starts to increase.

572
00:46:38,170 --> 00:46:42,920
True. We don't have a cure.

573
00:46:44,310 --> 00:46:50,960
All we can do is maintain a low temperature and stall time with tranquilizers and sleeping pills.

574
00:46:50,960 --> 00:46:53,930
Chairman, you don't have much time left, either, right?

575
00:46:54,650 --> 00:46:56,820
Maximum a month?

576
00:46:56,820 --> 00:46:59,260
Your wife is the same, right?

577
00:46:59,260 --> 00:47:02,780
She got infected right around the same time as me.

578
00:47:02,780 --> 00:47:06,890
I thought that's why you said you would develop a cure within a month.

579
00:47:12,180 --> 00:47:15,530
I know very well how rushed you must feel, Chairman.

580
00:47:24,850 --> 00:47:28,940
I'm giving up on all the quarantined areas.

581
00:47:31,090 --> 00:47:34,230
You barely supported us all this time.

582
00:47:34,230 --> 00:47:38,160
As you mentioned, we can't have more infected people.

583
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:42,990
Let's shut off electricity, and don't pass out food.

584
00:47:42,990 --> 00:47:48,530
The ACs are on throughout the country. No need to waste energy.

585
00:47:49,610 --> 00:47:54,360
Shut off the electricity and wait for the infected to die on their own?

586
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:57,720
Even with a cure, there will be problems.

587
00:47:57,720 --> 00:48:03,240
We can't go easy on those who have tasted human blood already, just because it happened while they were sick.

588
00:48:03,240 --> 00:48:07,880
But, Sir, you're one of those who are addicted to the taste of blood.

589
00:48:07,880 --> 00:48:10,250
It's okay for me.

590
00:48:10,250 --> 00:48:13,430
I'm telling you this so you know it in advance.

591
00:48:13,430 --> 00:48:16,320
Since you seem to have a plan.

592
00:48:22,260 --> 00:48:23,900
Shouldn't we stop him?

593
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:25,860
If the electricity is shut off, the water will be shut off, too.

594
00:48:25,860 --> 00:48:27,960
People who are not infected will also end up dying.

595
00:48:27,960 --> 00:48:30,920
Find out when they're going to shut off the electricity.

596
00:48:41,260 --> 00:48:46,770
Hey, why do you think I married you?

597
00:48:46,770 --> 00:48:50,320
If you're my secretary, you should act like it and

598
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:51,930
fall in line without being told to!

599
00:48:51,930 --> 00:48:53,470
But we are married now.

600
00:48:53,470 --> 00:48:55,690
You and I can think differently.

601
00:48:55,690 --> 00:48:58,920
I still don't think I was wrong about it.

602
00:48:58,920 --> 00:49:02,500
So if we catch the disease, would you be accountable?

603
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:05,550
This is why I shouldn't have married an uneducated person.

604
00:49:05,550 --> 00:49:09,060
I think I made a mistake.

605
00:49:22,900 --> 00:49:25,590
- Dong Hyun, my phone. 
 - Geez!

606
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:29,040
Mom, I can give it back when I'm done recording.

607
00:49:29,040 --> 00:49:32,830
Mom, you strangely keep pestering me today. Is something on your phone?

608
00:49:32,830 --> 00:49:35,350
No such thing.

609
00:49:35,350 --> 00:49:37,440
Then wait a little longer.

610
00:49:37,440 --> 00:49:40,120
I'll go out and see if there's anything else going on. Okay?

611
00:49:40,120 --> 00:49:41,680
Hey, Dong Hyun...

612
00:49:41,680 --> 00:49:45,910
Mom! I'll give it back to you soon. Damn.

613
00:49:50,290 --> 00:49:53,830
I need something intense to get many hits.

614
00:49:58,590 --> 00:50:01,410
What's the old lady doing right now?

615
00:50:06,580 --> 00:50:08,500
Excuse me.

616
00:50:11,520 --> 00:50:14,290
You lost your cell phone, right?

617
00:50:14,290 --> 00:50:15,620
How do you know that?

618
00:50:15,620 --> 00:50:18,580
You dropped it on our way in. Right in front of the building.

619
00:50:18,580 --> 00:50:21,730
So how did you know that I was looking for it?

620
00:50:21,730 --> 00:50:26,010
You were recording something with it all the way back yesterday. You are still recording.

621
00:50:26,010 --> 00:50:28,360
I thought you might be looking for it.

622
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:31,940
Wait, wait... Lee Bo Ram?

623
00:50:35,070 --> 00:50:37,610
Will you help me out?

624
00:50:37,610 --> 00:50:38,920
I'm not going outside.

625
00:50:38,920 --> 00:50:40,630
I'll pay you.

626
00:50:40,630 --> 00:50:42,820
Don't you need money?

627
00:50:45,250 --> 00:50:49,040
Let me know if you need anything.

628
00:50:49,040 --> 00:50:51,040
How about something like bullets?

629
00:50:51,040 --> 00:50:53,080
Do you think that would be allowed?

630
00:50:54,300 --> 00:50:57,490
Why are you so interested in military supplies?

631
00:50:59,550 --> 00:51:01,360
I'm interested in the end of the world.

632
00:51:01,360 --> 00:51:04,080
The earth is facing a crisis right now.

633
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:06,550
Even without infectious disease, climate change,

634
00:51:06,550 --> 00:51:12,880
global warming, nuclear war, artificial intelligence... The apocalypse isn't too far off.

635
00:51:14,410 --> 00:51:16,050
I see.

636
00:51:16,050 --> 00:51:20,370
So I'm in the middle of collecting all kinds of survival tools.

637
00:51:20,370 --> 00:51:23,000
I'm also collecting combat rations from different countries.

638
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:25,150
Did you collect a lot of them?

639
00:51:25,150 --> 00:51:27,100
Combat rations?

640
00:51:31,490 --> 00:51:35,000
Would you like to see my collection?

641
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:38,890
A collection? Shall I then?

642
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:06,530
Doesn't it break if you apply pressure?

643
00:52:07,970 --> 00:52:10,450
I'm not so sure.

644
00:52:13,080 --> 00:52:16,230
If you destroy that, your life will be destroyed as well.

645
00:52:16,230 --> 00:52:18,950
You have to watch it if you don't want to get kicked out.

646
00:52:18,950 --> 00:52:21,190
Are you here to annoy me?

647
00:52:21,190 --> 00:52:25,910
I wanted to clear the air. I wanted to help you, too,

648
00:52:25,910 --> 00:52:29,040
but you took the drug.

649
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:31,800
When did you ever help me?

650
00:52:35,110 --> 00:52:37,410
Drink this when you get thirsty.

651
00:52:38,170 --> 00:52:42,550
Only if you can't hold back. I came because I was worried about you.

652
00:52:42,550 --> 00:52:45,120
 - That's the hardest. 
 - Of course.

653
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:46,900
Let me know if you need anything.

654
00:52:46,900 --> 00:52:48,250
 I think it's a mental illness.

655
00:52:48,250 --> 00:52:49,460
 Isn't that crazy?

656
00:52:49,460 --> 00:52:50,950
 What do you mean by mental illness?

657
00:52:50,950 --> 00:52:52,800
 I'm sure he has it.

658
00:52:52,800 --> 00:52:54,420
 I can't believe you're my oppa.

659
00:52:54,420 --> 00:52:56,070
 Hey, think carefully.

660
00:52:56,070 --> 00:52:56,990

661
00:52:56,990 --> 00:52:59,290
I told you to be quiet.

662
00:53:02,620 --> 00:53:04,890
I comforted him as Building Representative.

663
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:09,570
I thought the young man would be struggling. All right then.

664
00:53:13,320 --> 00:53:15,230
Wait...

665
00:53:15,230 --> 00:53:19,930
I voted to throw him out earlier.

666
00:53:20,910 --> 00:53:23,650
He would remember, right?

667
00:53:23,650 --> 00:53:28,230
There are plenty of people for him to dislike more so I'm sure it's okay.

668
00:53:34,210 --> 00:53:38,060
You can't get infected through the air so don't worry about that.

669
00:53:38,060 --> 00:53:42,930
Watch him, and if he seems to feel extreme thirst,

670
00:53:42,930 --> 00:53:45,830
do not give him water and come up to the fifth floor right away.

671
00:53:45,830 --> 00:53:48,130
- Got it? 
 - Okay. 
 - Okay.

672
00:53:48,130 --> 00:53:50,750
And this is the key for his handcuffs.

673
00:53:54,790 --> 00:53:58,190
You won't need it, but just in case.

674
00:53:59,370 --> 00:54:03,920
I'll go talk to him for a minute.

675
00:54:08,370 --> 00:54:11,770
Hey, aren't you scared?

676
00:54:11,770 --> 00:54:14,940
It's not even your apartment. Why did you vote yes?

677
00:54:19,390 --> 00:54:21,840
What did you talk about with the building representative?

678
00:54:23,030 --> 00:54:26,880
Instead of that, the thing that you're curious about is...

679
00:54:26,880 --> 00:54:29,730
There are lots of things I'm curious about.

680
00:54:29,730 --> 00:54:31,920
The drug buyer.

681
00:54:35,100 --> 00:54:38,130
You know, the man in the hazmat suit?

682
00:54:38,820 --> 00:54:40,340
The one who voted last.

683
00:54:40,340 --> 00:54:43,720
 - You know how muscles form when you work out? 
 - Yes.

684
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:48,710
 If you take one pill, it's twice as effective as working out.

685
00:54:48,710 --> 00:54:51,700
 If you look, it's in a small pill form.

686
00:54:51,700 --> 00:54:53,670
The fifteenth floor.

687
00:55:01,810 --> 00:55:05,690
It was right there. I can't see it from here.

688
00:55:05,690 --> 00:55:06,810
Go quickly and come back.

689
00:55:06,810 --> 00:55:09,650
I'll watch from here.

690
00:55:12,450 --> 00:55:14,680
Let's move these.

691
00:55:22,350 --> 00:55:26,100

(T/N: 119 is the emergency telephone number, similar to 911)

692
00:55:40,270 --> 00:55:42,130
Student.

693
00:55:44,960 --> 00:55:46,750
Are you looking for something?

694
00:55:46,750 --> 00:55:49,130
Do you want me to help you?

695
00:56:13,660 --> 00:56:17,320
Sae Bom! Kim Seung Beom says...

696
00:56:22,180 --> 00:56:25,090
Seo Yoon, where is Sae Bom?

697
00:56:25,090 --> 00:56:28,420
She went up with the ahjussi from the 15th floor.

698
00:56:42,830 --> 00:56:45,790

699
00:56:45,790 --> 00:56:46,980
So pretty.

700
00:56:46,980 --> 00:56:52,330
Hyun Kyung, this is Jae Yeol. He's a great pianist.

701
00:56:52,330 --> 00:56:54,660
When you write a novel about music next time,

702
00:56:54,660 --> 00:56:57,720
you can get advice from Jae Yeol...

703
00:57:01,780 --> 00:57:04,180
Or just lent me some money.

704
00:57:04,180 --> 00:57:06,610
Aren't you even worried about your wife and children?

705
00:57:06,610 --> 00:57:08,670
Talk about that kind of stuff after the lockdown is lifted.

706
00:57:08,670 --> 00:57:11,700
I'm sure they're fine! Do you think something happened to them?

707
00:57:11,700 --> 00:57:12,710
I'm working right now.

708
00:57:12,710 --> 00:57:15,050
Hey, to put it bluntly, if you die here,

709
00:57:15,050 --> 00:57:16,870
your apartment becomes mine.

710
00:57:16,870 --> 00:57:20,870
But if I followed you in here to help you out, you should...

711
00:57:20,870 --> 00:57:24,320
It sounds like you want to kill me.

712
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:26,770
But then again, you were the same back then, too.

713
00:57:26,770 --> 00:57:29,510
You pushed me off the swing, and I got hurt!

714
00:57:29,510 --> 00:57:31,500
I can't pull my hair back because of this!

715
00:57:31,500 --> 00:57:33,790
Then, then, were you ever good to me?

716
00:57:33,790 --> 00:57:35,450
You gave me hepatitis in my senior year,

717
00:57:35,450 --> 00:57:36,880
and I delayed a year going to college!

718
00:57:36,880 --> 00:57:39,140
Blame it on your weak immunity!

719
00:57:39,140 --> 00:57:42,710
Do you know how it feels to speak formally to people who are the same age as me?

720
00:57:45,900 --> 00:57:48,080
Let's talk outside.

721
00:57:52,130 --> 00:57:54,940
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

722
00:57:54,940 --> 00:57:57,470
I'm not wishing you bad or anything.

723
00:57:57,470 --> 00:57:59,540
It's not like that.

724
00:57:59,540 --> 00:58:01,960
It's because I'm disappointed.

725
00:58:01,960 --> 00:58:04,700
Why are you so disappointed? Well?

726
00:58:05,730 --> 00:58:09,070
You received an inheritance when you got married, and they sent you to college.

727
00:58:09,070 --> 00:58:11,990
I received tuition for one semester.

728
00:58:11,990 --> 00:58:14,580
I paid for the rest myself.

729
00:58:14,580 --> 00:58:17,970
Still, I held it in and didn't say anything.

730
00:58:17,970 --> 00:58:22,160
And now you act like you left your money with me!

731
00:58:24,900 --> 00:58:26,870
I'm sorry.

732
00:58:26,870 --> 00:58:31,420
Let's not speak too crudely.

733
00:58:32,410 --> 00:58:35,150
We are still family.

734
00:58:35,150 --> 00:58:37,750
Family, my foot.

735
00:58:49,010 --> 00:58:50,670
It's safe here. Right?

736
00:58:50,670 --> 00:58:51,630
Where are you going?

737
00:58:51,630 --> 00:58:54,980
What? I hear some noise.

738
00:58:56,130 --> 00:58:59,040
Hey, it's okay. It's safe here.

739
00:59:15,560 --> 00:59:18,270
Hey! Come here!

740
00:59:18,270 --> 00:59:19,460
What's with you two?

741
00:59:19,460 --> 00:59:21,140
Hey! Hey!

742
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:23,300
Run away!

743
00:59:40,150 --> 00:59:42,850
I don't think anyone is there.

744
00:59:46,850 --> 00:59:49,120
Hey, don't open it.

745
00:59:50,810 --> 00:59:54,670
You always say "hey" to me. I'm your oppa.

746
01:00:08,240 --> 01:00:10,190
Did you get scared?

747
01:00:10,190 --> 01:00:13,400
Hey, don't worry. Your oppa is here.

748
01:00:55,500 --> 01:00:58,060
Is something going on out there?

749
01:01:03,400 --> 01:01:05,210
No...

750
01:01:11,130 --> 01:01:15,090
Sae Bom! Yoon Sae Bom!

751
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:21,650
Sae Bom is here, right?

752
01:01:23,370 --> 01:01:26,220
She's busy right now.

753
01:01:26,220 --> 01:01:29,100
She'll be right out. Wait just a moment.

754
01:01:31,510 --> 01:01:36,220
Did you take the drug? The one you bought at the gym?

755
01:01:42,550 --> 01:01:47,440
If you laid even a finger on Sae Bom, you're dead.

756
01:01:50,220 --> 01:01:56,070

757
01:02:03,450 --> 01:02:10,490

758
01:02:12,010 --> 01:02:14,700
 A person is missing because of you.

759
01:02:14,700 --> 01:02:18,200
 We have the power, but we need a person.

760
01:02:18,200 --> 01:02:21,080
 Someone who will do what we tell him to.

761
01:02:21,080 --> 01:02:24,040
 It's not as if my thirst is quenched when I drink water.

762
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:25,110
 It's Na Soo Min's phone.

763
01:02:25,110 --> 01:02:28,790
 The electricity in your building will be shut off tonight.

764
01:02:28,790 --> 01:02:30,810
 Hyung, you guard here.

765
01:02:30,810 --> 01:02:32,400
 I'm here to take Sae Bom.

766
01:02:32,400 --> 01:02:34,580
 I came here to find even a small possibility.

767
01:02:34,580 --> 01:02:38,860
 Even if we have to get her bit by an infected, if necessary.
